node.text: We're expanding @wildandwhole, which was founded by our very own @danielleprewett, and launching its new website. To celebrate, I threw down with Danielle and @chefkevingillespie on a hot tip off. The problem is that The Flip Flop Flesher screwed it all up when he rendered his judgment. Help me identify the true winner. (That’s me!) You can check out the new site at the link in my bio. #fueledbynature 🎥 by @signs_west

node.text: It’s officially available, ladies and gents. You’ll hear the best of my buddy Buck Bowden’s(@bowdenmikebuck) close call stories in our new immersive audio experience, MeatEater’s Campfire Stories: Close Calls. In this audio original, Buck (pictured above) is joined by fifteen others, including me, in telling tales about narrow misses and harrowing brushes with death ranging from coastal Alaska to the jungles of Central America. Get ready to pucker up, and I ain’t talking about kissing. Available now at the link in my bio. #fueledbynature

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Steven Rinella on July 17, 2021. May be an image of deer and nature.

node.text: As a species, mule deer are famously sensitive to disturbance. Environmental degradation and increased predation can drive significant population impacts in a hurry. On an individual level, however, you see some cases of tremendous resilience. This photo comes from a MeatEater Podcast listener up in Alberta. His roommate took this photo of a toughassed mule deer. It's unclear what happened to him. #fueledbynature

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Steven Rinella on July 16, 2021. May be an image of body of water.

node.text: Garbage grip-and-grin. We just did a river cleanup project near MeatEater world headquarters in conjunction with @simmsfishing and @troutunlimited. This was our second canoe load in just a mile or so of floating. This year’s low water is hard on fish but good for trash picking. #fueledbynature

node.text: We're expanding @wildandwhole, which was founded by our very own @danielleprewett, and launching its new website. To celebrate, I threw down with Danielle and @chefkevingillespie on a hot tip off. The problem is that The Flip Flop Flesher screwed it all up when he rendered his judgment. Help me identify the true winner. (That’s me!) You can check out the new site at the link in my bio. #fueledbynature 🎥 by @signs_west

node.text: If you want this gun, there’s no need to pry it from my cold dead hands. All you need to do is support our Montana Farm and Ranch Hunter Access Appreciation Sweepstakes that we’re holding in conjunction with TRCP. It’s a left-handed Weatherby Mark V chambered in 300 Weatherby. It’s been on a few adventures, including an appearance on Netflix. We’ve got a boatload of other prizes as well. All proceeds go toward thanking landowners who enroll their private ground in Montana’s public access program. It’s a great cause. Enter at the link in my bio. #fueledbynature
